  "text": "• . Thus, it is concluded that kenaf fibers promote the nucleation of the less common β-phase crystals which have higher impact strength and toughness [CITATION_1] providing thus a secondary reinforcing mechanism. The thermogravimetric analysis for PP and PLA composites as a function of the kenaf fiber content is presented in Figures 7 and 8 , respectively. The temperature scale starts from 150 • C to allow higher resolution of the temperature range we are interested in. No weight loss was observed below this temperature indicating that there was no water absorbed in the kenaf fibers. The main decomposition peak for PP was found at ∼448",
